description._content: Description: Office of J.P. Praslin District at Baie St. Anne, built in 1901. La Digue in the distance. "Alexandre" in the offing. Location: Praslin, Seychelles Date: 1901 Description: Cutting on North Coast Road. Road begun Sept. 1902. Location: Seychelles Date: September 1902 Our Catalogue Reference: Part of CO 1069/771 This image is part of the Colonial Office photographic collection held at The National Archives. Feel free to share it within the spirit of the Commons Please use the comments section below the pictures to share any information you have about the people, places or events shown. We have attempted to provide place information for the images automatically but our software may not have found the correct location. For high quality reproductions of any item from our collection please contact our image library
